-HEY.
-HELLO. HOW ARE YOU?

02:37.400 --> 02:38.470
-PRETTY GOOD. HOW ARE YOU?
-GOOD.

02:38.500 --> 02:39.940
-IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.
-YEAH, YOU, TOO.

02:39.970 --> 02:41.610
-ARE YOU READY?
-YEAH. YOU?

02:41.640 --> 02:44.070
IN-OOH!

02:44.110 --> 02:45.340
BOOM.

02:45.380 --> 02:46.780
THANKS AGAIN
FOR TAKING HIM.

02:46.810 --> 02:48.210
CITY PARK IS ONE
OF HIS FAVORITES.

02:48.250 --> 02:49.710
YEAH, IT'S NO PROBLEM.
I'M JUST HAPPY

02:49.750 --> 02:51.450
TO BE SPENDING TIME
WITH MY LITTLE BUDDY.

02:51.480 --> 02:53.120
-DEFINITELY. HIGH-FIVE.
-HIGH-FIVE.

02:53.150 --> 02:54.620
YOU HAVE
YOUR OVERNIGHT STUFF?

02:54.650 --> 02:55.850
OKAY.

02:55.890 --> 02:57.120
HAVE FUN, YOU TWO.

02:57.160 --> 02:58.160
THANK YOU.

02:58.190 --> 03:00.160
-LET'S DO THIS.
-LET'S DO IT.

03:00.190 --> 03:03.660
-I LOVE YOU, MOM.
-I LOVE YOU, BLUE.

03:03.700 --> 03:05.160
-SEE YOU.
-BYE.

03:05.200 --> 03:07.100
SO...

03:07.130 --> 03:09.370
♪ MOVING AND GROOVING,
AND I CAN'T GET ENOUGH ♪

03:09.400 --> 03:11.340
♪ FEELS SO GOOD ♪

03:11.370 --> 03:13.870
♪ THAT WE'RE MOVING AND
GROOVING, CAN'T GET ENOUGH ♪

03:13.910 --> 03:16.110
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

03:16.140 --> 03:18.380
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

03:18.410 --> 03:21.380
♪♪

03:21.410 --> 03:23.380
♪ COME ON, DO YOU FEEL IT? ♪

03:23.420 --> 03:25.420
HEY, MOM.
WHAT'S UP?

03:25.450 --> 03:27.420
DARLENE:
Hey, Darla. How are you?

03:27.450 --> 03:31.260
You won't believe who I ran into
at the coffee shop.

03:31.290 --> 03:34.390
Your best friend is in town --
Jordan.

03:34.430 --> 03:36.890
JORDAN'S IN TOWN.

03:36.930 --> 03:38.960
WE HAVEN'T BEEN IN CONTACT
FOR YEARS.

03:39.000 --> 03:40.930
Of all your friends,
she was my favorite.

03:40.970 --> 03:42.700
YES, I KNOW YOU'VE ALWAYS
LIKED HER,

03:42.740 --> 03:44.940
BUT IT'S
REALLY SHORT NOTICE,

03:44.970 --> 03:46.800
AND I'M SUPER BUSY.

03:46.840 --> 03:48.670
IS SOMETHING WRONG,
DARLA?

03:48.710 --> 03:50.810
NO, NOTHING'S WRONG.
I'M JUST --

03:50.840 --> 03:53.240
[ SIGHS ]

03:53.280 --> 03:55.210
WHAT'S HER NUMBER?

03:55.250 --> 04:00.050
♪♪

04:00.090 --> 04:03.450
FOR YOU, FOR...

04:03.490 --> 04:06.790
YOUR BIRTHDAY.

04:06.830 --> 04:08.530
BIRTHDAY'S NOT
UNTIL NEXT WEEK.

04:08.560 --> 04:12.100
I KNOW. I, UM...

04:12.130 --> 04:16.430
IF -- IF I CHANGE MY MIND,
I DIDN'T WANT TO WAIT

04:16.470 --> 04:20.900
TO TRY AND THANK YOU
FOR THE OTHER DAY,

04:20.940 --> 04:22.840
FOR YOUR HELP.

04:22.880 --> 04:25.340
♪♪

04:25.380 --> 04:27.910
THANK YOU, CHARLEY.

04:27.950 --> 04:30.450
♪♪

04:30.480 --> 04:31.980
I DON'T THINK MY BIRTHDAY
IS GONNA BE MUCH

04:32.020 --> 04:34.850
TO CELEBRATE THIS YEAR.

04:34.890 --> 04:44.460
♪♪

04:44.500 --> 04:46.000
SO, THE DECISION
ON THE HIGHWAYS,

04:46.030 --> 04:49.570
PROP "K," IS COMING SOON.

04:49.600 --> 04:54.070
ONCE IT HITS, I'M BACK
IN CAMPAIGN MODE, NONSTOP.

04:54.110 --> 04:58.580
SO, UH, THIS IS SORT OF
THE LAST CHANCE TO...

04:58.610 --> 05:00.640
DO A LITTLE GETAWAY.

05:00.680 --> 05:03.780
♪♪

05:03.820 --> 05:05.850
YOU WANT TO COME WITH?

05:05.880 --> 05:08.890
♪♪

05:08.920 --> 05:10.890
YOU'RE GOING SOMEWHERE?

05:10.920 --> 05:12.490
SURE.

05:12.520 --> 05:14.220
WHY NOT, RIGHT?

05:14.260 --> 05:16.230
♪♪

05:16.260 --> 05:17.730
THEN I'D LOVE TO.

05:17.760 --> 05:19.130
OKAY.

05:19.160 --> 05:20.900
LET'S GO, THEN.

05:20.930 --> 05:22.970
♪♪

05:23.000 --> 05:25.170
[ CHUCKLES, SNIFFLES ]

05:28.910 --> 05:30.970
♪ LIFT OFF ♪

05:31.010 --> 05:32.610
♪ I'LL NEVER LET YOU FALL ♪

05:32.640 --> 05:35.050
♪♪

05:35.080 --> 05:36.950
♪ IT'S TOUGH, I KNOW ♪

05:36.980 --> 05:38.280
DIDN'T KNOW
YOU LIKED THIS SONG.

05:38.320 --> 05:40.050
♪ BUT WE GIVE IT OUR ALL ♪

05:40.090 --> 05:42.020
♪♪

05:42.050 --> 05:45.560
♪ I WANNA USE
ALL MY TIME ON YOU ♪

05:45.590 --> 05:48.230
♪ LESS IS NEVER MORE ♪

05:48.260 --> 05:50.130
SO, HOW ARE YOU DOING?

05:50.160 --> 05:52.460
♪♪

05:52.500 --> 05:54.060
BETTER.

05:54.100 --> 05:56.270
♪♪

05:56.300 --> 06:00.340
THANK YOU FOR, UH --
FOR TAKING CARE OF ME

06:00.370 --> 06:03.770
AND FOR WRITING
THAT COUNTER-ARTICLE.

06:03.810 --> 06:07.240
I APPRECIATE YOU USING YOUR NEW
CELEBRITY POWER FOR GOOD.

06:07.280 --> 06:12.150
♪♪

06:12.180 --> 06:14.650
SO, HAVE YOU HEARD
ABOUT THE MILL?

06:14.690 --> 06:16.250
WHAT'D THE INSURANCE
COMPANY SAY?

06:16.290 --> 06:17.550
THEY WON'T COVER IT

06:17.590 --> 06:21.320
SINCE THE POLICE SUSPECT
IT'S ARSON.

06:21.360 --> 06:23.360
I NEED TO FIND PROOF
OF FRANCES BOUDREAUX

06:23.400 --> 06:27.630
AND OLD WORLD ENERGY'S
CONNECTION TO THE FIRE.

06:27.670 --> 06:30.100
OLD WORLD ENERGY?

06:30.140 --> 06:34.270
SOUNDS LIKE A PLACE
WHERE BAD THINGS HAPPEN.

06:34.310 --> 06:37.410
YOU KNOW I CAN HELP
WITH ALL THIS.

06:37.440 --> 06:38.880
OLD WORLD ENERGY.

06:38.910 --> 06:40.780
DIG A LITTLE.

06:40.810 --> 06:42.450
I'M STILL A JOURNALIST.

06:42.480 --> 06:45.080
I CAN GET AT
THE REAL STORY.

06:45.120 --> 06:47.480
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO ALL THIS
ON YOUR OWN.

06:47.520 --> 06:53.690
♪♪

06:53.730 --> 06:55.590
Hostess:
CEDAR AND OAK WOMEN'S RETREAT

06:55.630 --> 07:00.360
BELIEVES IN THE REJUVENATING
POWER OF NATURE.

07:00.400 --> 07:04.370
WE OFFER GUIDED MEDITATIONS,
RAW MEALS,

07:04.400 --> 07:07.440
HIKES TO OUR NATURAL
HOT SPRINGS,

07:07.470 --> 07:11.140
ALL YOU NEED
TO EXPEL NEGATIVE ENERGY.

07:11.180 --> 07:12.440
NO DISTRACTIONS.

07:12.480 --> 07:16.680
JUST YOU AND NATURE.

07:16.720 --> 07:20.280
WELL, THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT WE NEED, RIGHT?

07:20.320 --> 07:22.220
RIGHT.
THANK YOU FOR THIS.

07:22.250 --> 07:23.690
IT'S VERY COOL.

07:23.720 --> 07:25.660
WELCOME HOME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:25.690 --> 07:31.730
♪♪

07:31.760 --> 07:37.330
♪♪

07:37.370 --> 07:39.770
COZY.

07:39.810 --> 07:41.670
-THANK YOU.
-MM-HMM.

07:41.710 --> 07:43.510
IS THERE
A RESTROOM NEARBY?

07:43.540 --> 07:46.810
OH, THE OUTHOUSES ARE
DOWN THAT PATH RIGHT THERE.

07:46.850 --> 07:50.380
NOW, I AM GOING TO LEAVE YOU TWO
TO GET SETTLED IN.

07:50.420 --> 07:56.550
♪♪

07:56.590 --> 07:59.160
RUSTIC.

07:59.190 --> 08:03.430
IT'S LIKE WHEN WE WERE LITTLE,
CAMPING WITH DADDY, RIGHT?

08:03.460 --> 08:05.200
SURE IS.

08:05.230 --> 08:07.700
♪♪

08:07.730 --> 08:09.270
OKAY.

08:09.300 --> 08:11.170
HA! CHA!

08:11.200 --> 08:13.200
CHA! CHA! CHA!
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

08:13.240 --> 08:14.240
[ LAUGHS ]

08:14.270 --> 08:15.610
CHA! CHA!

08:15.640 --> 08:16.910
YOU'RE SUCH A HAM, BLUE.

08:16.940 --> 08:19.280
VIRGINIA SALTED?

08:19.310 --> 08:21.280
THAT ONE'S SO FUNNY.
YEAH.

08:21.310 --> 08:22.710
CAN YOU SEND THESE
TO MY POPS?

08:22.750 --> 08:24.250
AND I WANT TO SHOW IT
TO MY FRIEND JOIE.

08:24.280 --> 08:25.620
YEAH, SURE.

08:25.650 --> 08:27.950
YOU KNOW, I THINK I MET HER MOM
A COUPLE WEEKS AGO --

08:27.990 --> 08:29.520
MS. DEESHA, RIGHT?

08:29.560 --> 08:31.560
YEAH, YEAH.
UH-HUH. SHE'S PRETTY COOL.

08:31.590 --> 08:33.120
YOU LIKE HER?

08:33.160 --> 08:35.190
I THINK POPS
LIKES MS. DEESHA.

08:35.230 --> 08:38.500
YEAH?
LIKE,<i> LIKES</i> MS. DEESHA.

08:38.530 --> 08:40.300
YOU COOL WITH THAT?

08:40.330 --> 08:43.400
[ CAROUSEL MUSIC PLAYING ]

08:43.440 --> 08:45.400
YOU KNOW, BLUE, I REMEMBER
WHEN MY PARENTS

08:45.440 --> 08:48.310
STARTED HANGING OUT
WITH OTHER PEOPLE.

08:48.340 --> 08:50.240
AT FIRST, IT MADE ME SAD,
'CAUSE I THOUGHT IT MEANT

08:50.280 --> 08:53.140
THAT WE WEREN'T GONNA SPEND
ANY TIME TOGETHER.

08:53.180 --> 08:55.250
BUT I MET THE OTHER PEOPLE,

08:55.280 --> 08:59.050
AND THEY WERE NICE, YOU KNOW?

08:59.080 --> 09:03.420
I THINK THAT MY MOM AND DAD
ARE ACTUALLY HAPPIER.

09:03.460 --> 09:08.490
SO YOU DIDN'T
FEEL SAD ANYMORE...EVER?

09:08.530 --> 09:10.790
SOMETIMES.

09:10.830 --> 09:12.800
SOMETIMES,
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

09:12.830 --> 09:14.860
♪♪

09:14.900 --> 09:17.530
THERE'S A BRIGHT SIDE --
A BIG ONE.

09:17.570 --> 09:20.600
WHAT?
YOU GET TWO CHRISTMASES.

09:20.640 --> 09:22.810
YOU GET TWO
BIRTHDAY PRESENTS.

09:22.840 --> 09:26.540
YOU GET TWO GRADUATION PARTIES
ONCE I GET MY COLLEGE LETTERS.

09:26.580 --> 09:29.180
AND YOU GET TWO SEPARATE ROOMS
THAT YOU CAN DECORATE

09:29.210 --> 09:30.850
AND -- AND --
AND PLAY IN.

09:30.880 --> 09:33.320
DOUBLE PRESENTS
IS PRETTY AWESOME.

09:33.350 --> 09:35.420
IT IS.

09:35.450 --> 09:37.690
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT, MAN?
IF YOU EVER FEEL SAD,

09:37.720 --> 09:39.290
THAT'S OKAY.

09:39.320 --> 09:42.590
I JUST WANT YOU TO CALL ME
IF YOU DO, OKAY?

09:42.630 --> 09:44.530
OKAY.
YOU PROMISE?

09:44.560 --> 09:46.030
PROMISE.
YOU'RE GONNA CALL ME?

09:46.060 --> 09:48.530
DEAL.
ALRIGHT, DEAL.

10:02.510 --> 10:04.210
REMY.

10:09.520 --> 10:10.820
I KNOW IT'S HARD
FOR YOU TO HEAR,

10:10.860 --> 10:13.160
BUT I DID HAVE
GENUINE FEELINGS FOR HIM.

10:15.290 --> 10:19.700
YOU'D BROKEN UP WITH HIM,
AND YOU TWO NEVER, YOU KNOW...

10:21.930 --> 10:24.970
WE NEVER SLEPT TOGETHER?

10:25.000 --> 10:29.510
RIGHT, SO I HONESTLY FELT
LIKE IT COULD BE OKAY.

10:29.540 --> 10:33.910
PROBLEM WAS I DIDN'T
TALK WITH YOU FIRST.

10:33.950 --> 10:35.010
IT'S THE SAME
WITH THE BOOK.

10:35.050 --> 10:39.750
I ACTED BEFORE COMMUNICATING
WITH YOU.

10:39.790 --> 10:43.750
AND I DON'T WANT TO EVER
DO THAT AGAIN, CHARLEY.

10:43.790 --> 10:45.060
EVER.

10:51.760 --> 10:54.160
NOVA...

10:55.870 --> 11:00.200
...I DON'T THINK I'VE EVER
FULLY UNDERSTOOD YOU.

11:02.970 --> 11:04.670
I'VE WANTED YOU TO.

11:09.480 --> 11:12.920
WHY DO YOU THINK YOU RUSH
IN LIKE THAT?

11:12.950 --> 11:17.620
I MEAN, WHAT'S GOING ON
THAT YOU DO THAT?

11:20.830 --> 11:22.990
TRYING TO FIGURE IT OUT.

11:25.600 --> 11:29.170
I-I THINK IF --

11:29.200 --> 11:31.970
IF I'M HONEST,
SOMETHING AUNT VI SAID EARLIER

11:32.000 --> 11:36.710
GOT ME REALLY THINKING,
AND SHE'S RIGHT.

11:36.740 --> 11:39.480
I DIDN'T WANT YOUR "NO"

11:39.510 --> 11:43.580
TO STOP ME FROM DOING
WHAT I WANTED TO DO.

11:43.620 --> 11:47.250
DEEP DOWN, I GUESS I SUSPECTED
YOU'D DISAPPROVE OF ME AND REMY.

11:49.420 --> 11:51.250
I WANTED TO EXPLORE
A RELATIONSHIP WITH HIM,

11:51.290 --> 11:53.790
SO I JUMPED IN
BEFORE YOU COULD SAY NO.

11:56.230 --> 11:59.600
IT'S THE SAME
WITH THE BOOK, MAYBE.

11:59.630 --> 12:02.370
SO YOU'RE OF THE SCHOOL
THAT IT'S BETTER

12:02.400 --> 12:04.900
TO ASK FOR FORGIVENESS

12:04.940 --> 12:08.510
THAN PERMISSION?

12:08.540 --> 12:10.270
HOW'D THAT WORK OUT?

12:15.810 --> 12:17.910
I HEAR YOU.

12:17.950 --> 12:22.390
THIS IS A FLAW IN ME
THAT I HAVE TO CORRECT.

12:22.420 --> 12:25.020
AND I WILL.

12:25.060 --> 12:26.690
I PROMISE.

12:32.800 --> 12:34.430
I WENT OUT WITH MY COWORKERS
LAST NIGHT

12:34.470 --> 12:37.770
TO THIS LAME-ASS
CONFERENCE RECEPTION.

12:37.800 --> 12:40.040
IT WAS LIKE
A BOOTLEG COTILLION.

12:40.070 --> 12:41.810
[ LAUGHS ]

12:41.840 --> 12:44.310
REMEMBER THOSE UGLY DRESSES
WE HAD TO WEAR?

12:44.340 --> 12:46.510
I'M CONVINCED OUR MOTHERS
WANTED US TO GROW UP

12:46.550 --> 12:48.950
TO BE MORE MISERABLE
THAN THEM.

12:48.980 --> 12:52.620
YES, I'VE, UH --
I'VE HAD THE SAME THOUGHT.

12:52.650 --> 12:55.190
AND I'M SO READY TO GET
THE HELL OUT OF D.C.

12:55.220 --> 12:57.090
YOU'RE LUCKY YOU LEFT.

12:57.120 --> 13:00.790
EVERY PARTY, IT'S THE SAME
TIRED GUYS WHO WORK ON THE HILL.

13:00.830 --> 13:02.130
I DON'T KNOW.

13:02.160 --> 13:04.960
I'VE SERIOUSLY BEEN EYEING
NEW ORLEANS.

13:05.000 --> 13:06.830
WHAT?
YEAH.

13:06.870 --> 13:08.570
HOW DO YOU LIKE IT
DOWN HERE?

13:08.600 --> 13:10.130
I LIKE IT.

13:10.170 --> 13:13.540
SAINT JO IS NICE,

13:13.570 --> 13:15.870
QUIET, SLOW.

13:15.910 --> 13:17.740
RIGHT.

13:17.780 --> 13:21.910
YOU MUST BE OUT
IN NEW ORLEANS LIKE EVERY NIGHT.

13:21.950 --> 13:25.180
SO, WHERE'S
THE PARTY TONIGHT?

13:25.220 --> 13:27.680
I REALLY DON'T KNOW.

13:27.720 --> 13:29.250
I'M NOT ABOUT
THAT LIFE ANYMORE.

13:29.290 --> 13:31.190
NOT ABOUT THAT LIFE?

13:31.220 --> 13:32.420
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

13:32.460 --> 13:35.690
WE BASICALLY INVENTED
GETTING TURNT.

13:35.730 --> 13:36.860
Waitress: HERE YOU GO.

13:36.900 --> 13:39.030
THANK YOU.

13:39.060 --> 13:40.460
NOT GETTING A DRINK?

13:40.500 --> 13:43.800
OH, RIGHT. YOUR MOM MENTIONED
YOU'RE ALL DRY NOW.

13:43.840 --> 13:47.040
YOU DON'T MIND IF I HAVE
A LITTLE FUN, DO YOU?

13:47.070 --> 13:49.070
IT'S FINE.

13:49.110 --> 13:50.170
<i> I'M</i> FINE.

13:50.210 --> 13:51.470
MM.

13:51.510 --> 13:53.240
I'M GONNA SLOW DOWN, TOO,

13:53.280 --> 13:55.380
ONE DAY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:55.410 --> 13:58.680
WE USED TO GET SO LIT.

13:58.720 --> 14:01.250
OH, MY GOD. REMEMBER THAT NIGHT
IN GEORGETOWN

14:01.290 --> 14:03.050
AT THOMAS CAINE'S
HOUSE PARTY?

14:03.090 --> 14:05.420
YOU AND YOUR MAN AT THE TIME --
WHAT WAS HIS NAME?

14:05.460 --> 14:07.460
RALPH ANGEL.
YOU SAID Y'ALL WERE ON A BREAK,

14:07.490 --> 14:09.760
BUT I KNOW YOU JUST WANTED
TO PARTY,

14:09.790 --> 14:13.130
WHICH WAS SO WORTH IT,
BECAUSE IT WAS EPIC.

14:13.160 --> 14:14.830
WHAT DID WE EVEN TAKE
THAT NIGHT?

14:14.870 --> 14:17.500
WHATEVER IT WAS HAD US
SO OUT OF OUR MINDS.

14:17.540 --> 14:19.640
THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

14:19.670 --> 14:21.340
SEVEN, EIGHT YEARS?

14:21.370 --> 14:25.140
WHATEVER IT WAS, STILL ONE
OF THE BEST NIGHTS EVER.

14:25.180 --> 14:27.140
ONE MINUTE, YOU WERE
DOWNING JELL-O SHOTS,

14:27.180 --> 14:29.510
AND THE NEXT, YOU AND TOM
WERE ALL OVER EACH OTHER.

14:29.550 --> 14:31.810
Y'ALL GAVE US QUITE
THE "X"-RATED SHOW,

14:31.850 --> 14:34.050
WELL, BEFORE
HE DRAGGED YOU UPSTAIRS.

14:34.090 --> 14:36.590
PEOPLE SAW US?
EVERYBODY SAW.

14:36.620 --> 14:39.120
Y'ALL WERE BUCK-WILD.
GET IT, GIRL.

14:39.160 --> 14:41.720
NEXT THING I KNOW,
TOM WAS OLD NEWS.

14:41.760 --> 14:43.830
ALL ABOUT YOU AND CHASE.

14:43.860 --> 14:44.960
HE TOOK YOU
TO THE BATHROOM,

14:45.000 --> 14:46.700
AND YOU GUYS WERE IN THERE
FOR LIKE AN HOUR.

14:46.730 --> 14:50.500
I HAD TO PEE SO BAD. UGH.
CHASE.

14:50.540 --> 14:52.270
CHASE LIVESTONE?

14:52.300 --> 14:55.370
I DON'T --

14:55.410 --> 14:57.070
I-I DON'T REMEMBER HIM
BEING THERE.

14:57.110 --> 15:00.180
YEAH, THAT'S HOW
MESSED UP YOU WERE.

15:00.210 --> 15:01.980
UM...

15:02.010 --> 15:04.910
I -- I'VE LOST TRACK
OF TIME,

15:04.950 --> 15:06.450
AND, UH, I HAVE TO GO.

15:06.480 --> 15:07.650
YOU OKAY?
OKAY, I GOTTA RUN.

15:07.690 --> 15:09.550
I GOTTA PICK UP MY SON.

15:15.530 --> 15:17.690
[ SIREN WAILS ]

15:17.730 --> 15:20.630
♪♪

15:20.670 --> 15:23.000
[ CAR HORN BLARES ]

15:23.030 --> 15:30.270
♪♪

15:30.310 --> 15:35.310
♪♪

15:35.330 --> 15:37.510
Y ]

